---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TwoColumnLayout from "../layouts/TwoColumnLayout.astro";
import Ornament from "../components/Ornament.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Colophon">
  <TwoColumnLayout>
    <article>
      <h1>Colophon</h1>
      <p class="meta-text">How this site is made</p>
      <p>
        This page describes the tools, processes, and decisions behind
        chrisbusse.com. If you're reading an article and wondering how it
        was produced, this is the place.
      </p>

      <Ornament glyph="☙" />

      <h2>On AI-Assisted Writing</h2>
      <p>
        Some of the writing on this site is developed with AI assistance,
        primarily Claude by Anthropic. I treat AI the way a researcher treats
        a librarian or a writer treats an editor: the tool extends my reach,
        but the accountability is mine.
      </p>
      <p>
        The degree of AI involvement varies by piece. Some begin as broad
        research prompts where the AI surfaces sources and synthesizes
        background material that I then shape into an argument. Others are
        pair-written through iterative conversation, with the AI drafting
        and me directing. Some I write entirely myself.
      </p>
      <p>
        Where AI contributed meaningfully, I note it in a process colophon
        at the end of the article. I do this not because the norms require
        it yet&mdash;they are still forming&mdash;but because I believe
        transparency about process is a prerequisite for trust. The words
        published under my name reflect my judgment, my editorial choices,
        and my willingness to stand behind them. How they were produced is
        something you deserve to know.
      </p>

      <Ornament glyph="☙" />

      <h2>Technology</h2>
      <p>
        This site is built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a>,
        a static site generator that ships zero JavaScript by default.
        The source code is written with assistance from Claude and Cursor.
        Content is authored in Markdown and rendered at build time.
      </p>

      <Ornament glyph="☙" />

      <h2>AI Agents</h2>
      <p>
        Beyond AI-assisted writing, this site uses autonomous AI agent
        sessions&mdash;called <a href="/gnomes">Gnomes</a>&mdash;for
        content operations like pace layer classification and image
        description. Each Gnome operates within defined boundaries and
        leaves a traceable record of its work. See the
        <a href="/gnomes">Gnomes</a> page for the full system
        documentation.
      </p>

      <Ornament glyph="☙" />

      <h2>Typography</h2>
      <p>
        Headings are set in <a href="https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Rokkitt">Rokkitt</a>,
        a slab serif by Vernon Adams. Body text uses
        <a href="https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Spectral">Spectral</a>,
        a serif designed for screen reading by Production Type. Interface
        elements and metadata use
        <a href="https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Roboto+Mono">Roboto Mono</a>
        by Christian Robertson.
      </p>
    </article>
  </TwoColumnLayout>
</BaseLayout>
